First, we need to find the intersection of sets A and B, which is represented by A∩B. 

A∩B = {x | x ∈ A and x ∈ B}
A∩B = {2, 3}

Now, we need to find the Cartesian product of A∩B and the set {5}. The Cartesian product of two sets A and B, denoted by A×B, is the set of all ordered pairs (a, b) such that a ∈ A and b ∈ B.

(A∩B) × {5} = {(2, 5), (3, 5)}

So, the Cartesian product of A∩B and the set {5} is {(2, 5), (3, 5)}.
